      "description": "Per the project V&V plan (Rev C, §4.2), validation of the FEA compression-bending model against physical hardware shall be accomplished by means of a controlled experiment in which specimen assignment, loading conditions, and measurement protocol are defined a priori and held invariant across all test articles. A controlled-experiment design is required to ensure that sources of variability are attributable to the model rather than to uncontrolled test-setup differences, and to satisfy FDA guidance on bench-test reproducibility for Class II spinal implants.",
